<subSubSection id="09AB84DA420E8956FF755FE0FD86C59C" pageId="9" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="410ED751420E8956FF755FE0FE98C485" blockId="9.[227,348,1199,1225]" box="[227,348,1199,1225]" pageId="9" pageNumber="19">
<heading id="1A46603D420E8956FF755FE0FE98C485" bold="true" box="[227,348,1199,1225]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="19" reason="3">
<emphasis id="73C50B43420E8956FF755FE0FE98C485" bold="true" box="[227,348,1199,1225]" pageId="9" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="410ED751420E8956FF755F90FD86C59C" blockId="9.[225,1437,1246,1488]" pageId="9" pageNumber="19">
Species of 
<taxonomicName id="86B1ACD2420E8956FEC95F90FD8BC4B5" authorityName="Bensaid" authorityYear="1974" box="[351,591,1247,1273]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ponticeratidae" genus="Pseudoprobeloceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="9" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="73C50B43420E8956FEC95F90FD8BC4B5" box="[351,591,1247,1273]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="19">Pseudoprobeloceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reaching about 
<quantity id="86497AB4420E8956FC9F5F91FC9EC4B5" box="[777,858,1246,1273]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="50.0">50 mm</quantity>
conch diameter with thinly discoidal, subinvolute conch at 
<quantity id="86497AB4420E8956FEDC5E4CFE58C551" box="[330,412,1283,1309]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
dm (ww/dm ~ 0.35; uw/dm ~ 0.28); coiling rate moderate (WER ~ 1.95). Whorl profile weakly compressed (ww/wh ~ 0.85); umbilical wall oblique, umbilical margin broadly rounded, venter weakly flattened, ventrolateral shoulder narrowly rounded. Growth lines very fine, strongly biconvex with linguiform ventrolateral projection. Suture line with V-shaped external lobe with diverging flanks; median saddle low, E 
<subScript id="DD35D514420E8956FE745EEAFE2FC5FF" attach="left" box="[482,491,1445,1459]" fontSize="6" pageId="9" pageNumber="19">2</subScript>
lobe small, rounded, ventrolateral saddle almost symmetrically rounded, lateral lobe asymmetrically rounded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
